<!--
Traditional Chinese translation — full UI coverage. Display label is the
neutral "Chinese (Traditional)" / 中文（繁體）, never region-named, mirroring
the zh-rCN precedent (which displays "Chinese (Simplified)" rather than
naming the PRC). Casual register: 你 (informal "you") rather than 您 (formal),
bare imperatives without 請 ("開啟設定" rather than "請開啟設定") — same
spousal-tone register as zh-rCN.

Vocabulary leans Traditional-software-standard (predominantly Taiwan
usage, also broadly understood by HK readers via Android's `zh-Hant`
fallback chain): 設定 / 預設 / 新增 / 儲存 / 貼上 / 金鑰 / 資料 / 檔案
/ 使用者 / 介面 / 行事曆 / 行程 / 螢幕 / 程式 / 影片 / 訊息 / 機率
/ 重新整理. Where TW and HK forms diverge, the entry follows the form
that reads naturally in both (e.g. 通知, 權限, 完成, 取消).

What is NOT overridden, by design:
- `app_name` — brand identifier, identical across locales.
- `insight_time_am` / `_pm` / `_midnight` / `_noon` (and *_minutes
  variants) — English-only spoken-time formatter helpers. zh-TW uses
  `insight_time_hour` / `_hour_minutes` ("15點" / "15點30分") which
  are translated below; the AM/PM keys exist for the
  `Locale.language == "en"` path only and would never be read in a
  zh-TW runtime.

Typography conventions:
- Sentence-final period 。 (ideographic full stop), not Latin "."
- List enumeration uses 、 between items (not Latin comma)
- Quotes around nested labels use Traditional 「…」 corner brackets —
  the TW house style for primary quotation; nested quotes inside that
  would use 『…』 (none currently used in this file)
- Parentheses use full-width （ ） around Chinese content; Latin ( )
  only when the parenthetical is itself Latin script (e.g. URLs)
- Latin brand names ("ClothesCast", "Open-Meteo") and Latin URLs keep
  the conventional space-around-Latin spacing zh-Hant typography uses

Picker labels under `settings_region_language_*` and
`settings_tts_voice_locale_*` give the zh-TW names for every offered
locale (英文（美國）, 法文（加拿大）, 中文（繁體）, …). The locale tag stored
on disk (en-US / fr-CA / zh-TW) is unchanged; only the displayed
label localises.
-->
